Welcome to the total.js documentation. Total.js is free web application framework for building Web sites and Web applications using JavaScript, HTML and CSS.

##Installation options

- NPM (Node package manager)
- NPM (Node package manager) installation as global module
- Run the framework without installation
- Run empty project

**NPM (Node package manager)**

```bash
$npm install total.js
```

**NPM (Node package manager) installation as global module**

```bash
$npm install total.js
```

**Run the framework without installation**

Create `index.js` file, put below content and run `node index.js`.

```javascript
function init() {
    framework.http('debug');
}

require('http').get('http://modules.totaljs.com/total.js/v1.7.0/total.js', function(res) {
    var buffer = [];
    res.on('data', function(buf) { buffer.push(buf.toString('utf8')); });
    res.on('end', function() { eval(buffer.join('')); if (typeof(init) !== 'undefined') init(); });
});
```
